<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-2759] We should never open an IndexInput when an IndexOutput is still open</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-2759</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;I modified MockDirWrapper to assert this (except for&lt;br/&gt;
segments_N/segments.gen, where it&apos;s expected), and, it uncovered a&lt;br/&gt;
couple of places involving NRT readers where we open a shared doc&lt;br/&gt;
store file that&apos;s still open for writing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;First, if you install a merged segment warmer, we were failing to&lt;br/&gt;
force the merge of the doc stores in this case, thus potentially&lt;br/&gt;
opening the same doc stores that are also still open for writing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Second, if you&apos;re actively adding docs in other threads when you call&lt;br/&gt;
IW.getReader(), the other threads could sneak in and flush new&lt;br/&gt;
segments sharing the doc stores.  The returned reader then opens the&lt;br/&gt;
doc store files that are still open for writing.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
